<h2 class="pageTitle"><span>TeX and LaTeX</span></h2>

</div>
<div class="contentMain">


<div id="pageContent"><h3><strong>Windows XP, Vista, and 7</strong></h3>
<p><strong>MiKTex:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <a href="http://miktex.org/">http://miktex.org</a> and download the latest version.</li>
<li>Run the installer.</li>
<li>Install for all users.</li>
<li>Select where you want MikTex to be installed. If the default location is fine, click next.</li>
<li>Select your preferred paper size and install.</li>
</ol>
<p>To test, open a command prompt and type texify;  you should receive out put similar to : texify: Missing file argument.</p>
<p><strong>TeXnicCenter</strong> (a GUI TeX Editor):  </p>
<p>Note: MikTex must be installed for TeXnicCenter to work.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <a title="texniccenter download" href="http://www.texniccenter.org/resources/downloads/">http://www.texniccenter.org/resources/downloads/</a> and download the TeXnicCenter Installer.</li>
<li>Run the installer.</li>
<li>Select where you want TeXnicCenter to be installed. If the default location is fine, click next.</li>
<li>Select the Typical components and install.</li>
</ol>
<p>After installation, TeXnicCenter must be configured to use MikTex. The Configuration Wizard will prompt you for the distribution directory.</p>
<p>Select the location you installed MikText\miktex\bin.</p>
<p>Typically this will look like: C:\Program Files\MiKTeX 2.9\miktex\bin or C:\Program Files (x86)\MiKTeX2.9/miktex/bin</p>
<p>On the PostScript-Viewer configuration page, the form can be left blank.</p>
<h3><strong>Mac OS</strong></h3>
<p><strong>MacTex</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Download the current distribution of MacTeX from <a title="mactex download location" href="http://www.tug.org/mactex/">http://www.tug.org/mactex/</a>.</li>
<li>Run the installer.  </li>
</ol>
<p>To test your MacTex installation:</p>
<ol>
<li>Open a terminal.</li>
<li>Type latex -version</li>
<li>You should receive output similar to: pdfTeX 3.1415926-1.40.10-2.2 (TeX Live 2009)</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>TeXShop</strong> (a GUI TeX editor):</p>
<p>NOTE: MacTeX must be installed for TeXShop to work.</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to <a title="texshop download" href="http://pages.uoregon.edu/koch/texshop/obtaining.html">http://pages.uoregon.edu/koch/texshop/obtaining.html</a> and download the Latest TeXShop.</li>
<li>Double click the zip file if it did not unzip automatically, and open the TeXShop folder. Drag TeXShop to the Applications folder. Or: create the folder /Applications/TeX and install TeXShop there.</li>
</ol></div>

</div>
</div>


